******
[4] Congo DR (South Kivu)
Date: Mon 15 Sep 2014
Source: Radio Okapi [in French, machine transl., edited]
http://radiookapi.net/regions/sud-kivu/2014/09/15/sud-kivu-147-cas-de-cholera-enregistres-en-2-semaines-baraka-kazimiya-2-deces/


147 cholera cases, including 2 deaths, were recorded in 2 weeks in the cities of Baraka and Kazimiya in the area of health of Fizi in South Kivu. The chief physician of zone, Dr Asende Ehebelo who has delivered this information Sunday, 14 Sep 2014, indicates that the main cause is the lack of [clean] drinking water.

"The entire population relies on Lake Tanganyika for their water supply. We record at least 20 cases of cholera per day. To combat this outbreak, we sensitized the inhabitants of these 2 cities to comply with the rules of hygiene," said Dr Asende Ehebelo.

--
