[7] Cholera - Iraq (Kurdistan)
Date: Wed 17 Sep 2014
Source: BasNews [edited]
http://basnews.com/en/News/Details/Threat-of-Cholera-Outbreak-in-Refugee-Camps/34383


The Kurdistan Region's Ministry of Health has assured that there has been no cholera outbreak in any refugee camp in Kurdistan. However, there has been a warning about its outbreak outside the camps. Recently there were rumors circulated regarding a supposed cholera outbreak in the Domiz refugee camp in Duhok, which left people concerned.

Kurdistan's Ministry of Health spokesperson Khalis Qadr told BasNews that the rumors are not true and the likelihood of a cholera outbreak is not in the camps; rather, it is outside the camps. "We will continue to monitor the situation and we will try to prevent any threats of spreading the disease," said Qadr.

"The threat of cholera's outbreak is outside the refugee camps. This is due to sheltering refugees in inappropriate places like living in incomplete buildings without having access to basic needs like clean water which could lead to the spread of the bacterium."

Khalis Qadr stated that cholera usually spreads in September; otherwise, the threat of the spread of the disease will disappear.

Cholera outbreaks happen during the changing of the seasons, and there were reports of Cholera threat last year [2013] in Kurdistan which caused numerous people to die from the disease.

Cholera spreads due to the lack of access to clean water, especially in public places.

[Byline: Hoshmand Sadiq]

